<doc id="1330426" wikidata="Q1937652" url="?curid=1330426" title="Rouille">
<text>Rouille (; ) is a sauce that consists of egg yolk and olive oil with breadcrumbs, garlic, saffron and cayenne pepper. It is served as a garnish with fish and fish soup, notably bouillabaisse. Rouille is most often used in the cuisine of Provence.

==See also==
*Aioli
*Romesco
*Salvitxada

