<text>Pope Donus II is a non-existent pope who was at one time shown in the Annuario Pontificio. He was mistakenly inserted after Pope Benedict VI. The name comes from a confusion of the title &quot;domnus&quot; (&quot;dominus&quot;) and the Roman name &quot;Donus&quot; (&quot;LP&quot; II, XVIII, and 256).

